If you're not thinking
of buying one,

62
00:02:56,583 --> 00:02:58,583
it's gonna be real indecent
if a sales person

63
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:00,250
tries to come
and talk to you.

64
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:02,875
I'm not done! Hey!
Do you have to run?!

65
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:05,458
Where are you going now?! Stop!

66
00:03:08,583 --> 00:03:09,750
[SUBARU]
Flavor--medium strength...

67
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:11,208
[ISUZU]
What the crap?

68
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:12,791
I know what you're thinking.

69
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:15,416
These cozy little booths remind
you of your cockpit, don't they?

70
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:17,916
Don't stay here too long.
That would be indecent.

71
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,500
Noodle and run.

72
00:03:19,583 --> 00:03:22,583
[growls] Fine! Freak!

73
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:24,750
I'll let you get your
fix in my cockpit!

74
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,708
[SUBARU gasps]

75
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:28,916
Ah! Do ya mean it?

76
00:03:29,791 --> 00:03:31,125
[ISUZU]
Don't make me regret this.

77
00:03:31,208 --> 00:03:34,125
We'll figure out a plan
once we get to the Kerukeion.

78
00:03:34,208 --> 00:03:35,458
Let's go.

79
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:37,083
Are you freakin' kidding me?

80
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:38,708
Where the crust is my ship?!

81
00:03:38,791 --> 00:03:41,041
[PAC2-AR] Guess you can't just
park wherever you want, huh?

82
00:03:41,125 --> 00:03:43,791
[NARRATOR]
It was Space Age 0157.

83
00:03:43,875 --> 00:03:46,625
Although both brothers
had now lost their mechas,

84
00:03:46,708 --> 00:03:49,416
at the very least,
they had each other?

85
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:52,750
[beeping]

86
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:54,000
[PAC2-AR]
You've got mail!

87
00:03:54,083 --> 00:03:55,750
It's a message from
the <i>Tiramisu</i> !

88
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:57,750
[SUBARU gasps]
What's it say?

89
00:03:59,041 --> 00:04:00,208
[PAC2-AR]
"We've pinpointed the location

90
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:01,875
of the Durandal's crash landing.

91
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:06,208
Earth Union GHQ envoys are
on their way." Is that good?

92
00:04:06,291 --> 00:04:07,916
[ISUZU]
Earth Union Headquarters?

93
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,666
Craptastic.

94
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:10,958
So. When did they--

95
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:12,416
[crash]

96
00:04:15,625 --> 00:04:17,958
Look how rad their ship is.

97
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,791
[SOLDER 1A]
Ensign Ichinose of the <i>Tiramisu,</i>

98
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:23,375
I'm assuming that's
the Durandal?

99
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:26,500
Who's the powder puff
with the eye thingy?

100
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:29,000
My brother and I reunited here.

101
00:04:29,083 --> 00:04:30,250
He's a civilian!

102
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:31,291
[gasps]

103
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:39,208
How did I not know this before?

104
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:42,458
The Earth Union's general
headquarters is underwater?

105
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:45,416
Stay right here.
No funny business.

106
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:47,166
Understood.

107
00:04:49,416 --> 00:04:51,083
Tell me you saw that?

108
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:52,166
Saw what?

109
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:55,333
Look over there.
They have a gift shop!

110
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:56,708
[ISUZU]
That's stupid!

111
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:58,916
[NARRATOR] It was wisely
positioned at the entryway,

112
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:02,166
and was filled with the most
attractively packaged crap.

113
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:03,791
[ISUZU]
Who's in charge of inventory?

114
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:05,000
